    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-07-05T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-07-05T02:00:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">695A.0024/7–552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Korea (<persName corresp="#p_MJJ1"
                            type="from">Muccio</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pusan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-07-05T16:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 5, 1952—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>36. Eyes only <persName corresp="#p_AWPJ1">Armstrong</persName>–R. Re <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 992, June 23.<note n="1" xml:id="d208fn1"
                        >Not printed, but see footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_360">p. 360</ref>.</note>
                    Tel from <persName corresp="#p_MPW1">Manhard</persName>:</p>
                <p>Presume purpose “voluntary repatriation”, fundamentally Free World attempt
                    provide asylum to political refugees from Commie control. This presupposes
                    objective criteria to determine bona fide anti-Commies. Final, decision shld be
                    ours, not refugees.</p>
                <p>In Korea polling actually appeared as choice between two political allegiances
                    for <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POW’s</gloss> from divided countries. Polling
                    procedure super-imposed on background of extreme coercion and intimidation over
                    long period of both pro and anti-Commie leaders Korean compounds, anti-Commie
                    leaders Chi compounds. Physical safety all <gloss target="#t_POWs1"
                        >POW’s</gloss> immed before and during polling process not guaranteed due
                    lack internal control of compounds by UN guards. Honest naivete polling
                    questions resulted in involuntary repatriates and many involuntary
                    non-repatriates, choice being made in atmosphere of fear and uncertainty.
                    Simple, direct polling under these conditions invited Commie infiltration
                    anti-repatriation groups and enabled ambitious <gloss target="#t_POWs1"
                        >POW</gloss> leaders both factions attempt deliver vote in best wardheeling
                    manner to gain favor political superiors.</p>
                <p>In view continuing influence previous pro and anti-Commie <gloss
                        target="#t_POWs1">POW</gloss> leaders plus resumption CI and E reorientation
                    activities in present anti-repatriation camps, further polling by same method
                    under similar conditions will probably produce little if any numerical
                    shift.</p>
                <p>If repolling Chi <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POW’s</gloss> contemplated, recommend
                    separate detention all previous <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POW’s</gloss> leaders
                    now in power anti-repatriation compounds, official proclamation Commie amnesty
                    for <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POW’s</gloss> regardless of tattooing competitions,
                    etc., if such announcement available. Alert all alleged anti-repatriate Chi
                        <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POW’s</gloss> minus former leaders, trustees, and
                    those screened out voluntarily by intelligence agencies, for return mainland.
                    Provide sanctuary for all who subsequently attempt escape. Then announce new
                    plan Chi <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POW’s</gloss>, immed reclassify remainder as
                    political defectors from communism, no longer <gloss target="#t_POWs1"
                        >POW’s</gloss>. We thus formulate principle that we recognize right bona
                    fide <gloss target="#t_POWs1">POW’s</gloss> to be repatriated to give
                    controlling forces from which captured and right bona fide political refugees to
                    receive asylum from Commie control, whether found in combat zone or
                    elsewhere.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
